Members of the National Command Council will give details of government's interventions in various sectors later today. This after President Cyril Ramaphosa announced a 21-day nationwide lockdown. JOHANNESBURG - An Inter-Ministerial Committee dealing with coronavirus in South Africa will address the nation on Tuesday. This after President Cyril Ramaphosa’s address to the nation providing updates about COVID-19 in South Africa. COVID-19: 21-days lockdown explained Members of the National Command Council will brief the media on the details of government interventions in various sectors in response to the president’s address. The briefing will be done by the economic cluster. South Africa will be on lockdown from Thursday evening. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.